Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The Conservation Center is the largest and most comprehensive private art conservation laboratory in the country. With over 33 years of experience, The Center is a leader in the field of art preservation, evolving new treatments and methods to adapt to the rapidly-changing art world. They have cared for fine art from some of the country’s most prestigious private collections, museums, galleries, insurance companies, and corporations. Thier conservators are expertly trained in the treatment of paintings, works of art on paper, photographs, textiles, murals, antique and fine furniture, rare books, frames and gilding, objects, and sculpture.   The Center grew from a handful of painting conservators to more than 30 staff members with a wide range of specializations. In 2012, The Conservation Center moved from Chicago’s River North neighborhood to its new home in the Kinzie Industrial Corridor in West Town. With the help of Studio Gang Architects, they revitalized a late 19th century warehouse, previously used to store gold, into a state-of-the-art conservation laboratory.

The Company intends to launch the new sport at the Disney Wide World of Sports Arena in Orlando, Fl around August, 2020. This event will feature a 3 day tournament with the Championship Finals broadcast on ESPN2.   We also intend to build TriHockey into a diversified media company, centered around TriHockey content, including instructional videos, clinics, camps, interviews with players, clips from the TPHL matches, other short-form content, and more. Description: Survae is a geospatial media company. We provide digital asset management for video, imagery and associated data — with the context of maps.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Survae's map-based, data-driven platform offers powerful and intuitive ways to store, archive, search and retrieve, watch, observe change and share live and record video and other imagery — all with context. Metadata-based search and video playback make managing and sharing imagery simple. We connect all imagery to a set of base maps and  clients can then bring in any GIS map they want as a layer. Map formats we support include Esri shapefiles, kmz, and kml and the MISB format for video used by DoD, the intelligence community and the National System for Geospatial-Intelligence. Survae uniquely provides a platform that supports any organization that needs to view, manage, find and share a lot of video or imagery from multiple sources. Survae is built to support not only virtually any kind of data-enabled imagery from multiple devices, but also from disparate sources -- different service providers, internal and external users, and multiple viewpoints (aerial, ground, and submarine). Video, in particular, is difficult to share due to large file sizes. Survae’s cloud solution solves this problem by encoding all video files in web-standard formats and in a variety of sizes -- from 480p to 4k -- enabling shareable links to any media connected to the map. You can also embed Survae’s video/map player on any website or provide clients with private access to their own media where they can view, work with and share all of their content. Unlike other products, which are drone or camera-specific, Survae offers open support for aerial, ground and submarine video and imagery, providing an ideal solution for managing and working with the massive amount of images being recorded by UAVs and ground-based cameras. We are agnostic about the source as long as it’s data-enabled. We work with all kinds devices including UAVs, smartphones, GoPros and Garmins, police dash cams and body cams, surveillance cameras, underwater cameras, helicopter or plane-mounted cameras, plus satellites. Whether you are doing infrastructure inspections, managing conserved land or emergency response, Survae provides all the tools needed to acquire the needed imagery, view it with context, share it, and manage it using a map-based interface. The Survae platform is cloud-based. Custom integrations and APIs, private network installations and specialized camera and vehicle support are available.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Media and Entertainment, Navigation and Mapping, Video
